App:
An App in Salesforce is a collection of related components used for a particular business 
process.
Example:
A College Management App may contain:
Student Object
Faculty Object
Attendance Object
Course Object

Object:
An Object is used to store a specific type of information.
Example:
Student Object stores student data
Faculty Object stores faculty data

Record:
A Record is one individual entry inside an object.
Example:
Inside Student Object:
Sai
Ramesh
Sita
Each student becomes one record.

Field:
A Field stores one particular piece of information.
Example in Student Object:
Student Name
Roll Number
Branch
Phone Number

App	    College Management App
Object	Student Object
Record	One student’s details
Field	Student Name, Roll Number

Standard Objects

Standard Objects are the objects that are already available in Salesforce by default.
These objects are mainly used for common business activities like:
Customer management
Sales tracking
Service management

Custom Objects

Custom Objects are created by users when the required object is not available in Salesforce.
Businesses create custom objects according to their own needs.






Explanation of Objects

Student Object

This object stores information about students.

Fields:
Student Name
Roll Number
Branch
Phone Number
Faculty Object



This object stores faculty details.

Fields:
Faculty Name
Department
Subject
Course Object

This object stores course-related information.

Fields:
Course Name
Course ID
Credits
Attendance Object

This object stores attendance details of students.
 
Fields:
Attendance Percentage
Date
Student Reference